+    fn result_to_outcome_maps_verification_error_to_failed() {
+        // The fail-closed guarantee: every non-NoAttestations error becomes Failed,
+        // never NoAttestation. If this regresses, an attacker who causes a verify
+        // error (e.g. malformed bundle) would turn a hard failure into a soft
